'''Jill Pike''' (born 1981)<ref name="BUS"/> is an [[United States|American]] political commentator and activist who currently serves as deputy director of public affairs for the think tank [[Third Way (think tank)|Third Way]]. Formerly, she was one of the hosts of the [[talk radio]] show ''[[The Young Turks (talk show)|The Young Turks]]'' on [[Air America Radio]].<ref name="BUS">{{cite news|title= The Right Stuff from a Lefty Trio|url=http://www.businessweek.com/bwdaily/dnflash/feb2006/nf2006027_4397_db011.htm|first=Ronald|last=Grover|work=Business Week|accessdate=2006-10-16|year= 2006|unused_data= February 7,}}</ref>
Pike occasionally substitute hosted The Young Turks when either [[Cenk Uygur]] or [[Ben Mankiewicz]] was absent. Her roles on the show included booking guests and participating in the chat room.<ref name="LAT 2006">{{cite news|last=Gold|first=Matea|title=Can't get on the network? Get on the Net|url=http://articles.latimes.com/print/2006/mar/19/entertainment/ca-turks19|accessdate=July 10, 2011|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=March 19, 2006}}</ref> She formerly co-hosted an Internet-only broadcast following the show called ''Absolute Truth''. She is an outspoken atheist.<ref>{{cite web|author=26 April 2007|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RsR72LuZFrE&feature=channel_page|title=Abortion|publisher=YouTube|date=2007-04-26|accessdate=2010-01-01}}</ref> Pike has been a political opinion contributor to [[ABC News]].<ref name="ABCNews">{{cite news|title= Getting Beyond the Drama of Immigration Reform|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/story?id=2658451&page=1|first=Jill|last=Pike|work=ABC News|accessdate= 2006-11-26|year= 2006|unused_data= November 16,}}</ref><ref name="ABCNews2">{{cite news|title=The Issue Here Is That Dirty Little Word: 'Sex'|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/BothSidesAllSides/story?id=2853140&page=1|work=[[ABC News]]|first=Jill|last=Pike|date=February 6, 2007}}</ref> She is currently the Deputy Director for Public Affairs at [[Third Way (think tank)|Third Way]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thirdway.org/staff/26|title=Jill Pike|publisher=Third Way|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref>
Pike has a B.A. in Television Production from [[Loyola Marymount University]] and has worked behind the scenes in television in various capacities on such shows as ''National Enquirer TV'' and ''[[The Jeff Corwin Experience]]''. Referring to her modeling in a Young Turks calendar publication, her co-hosts say that "her calendar is a big hit among guys, of course."<ref name="USNEWS">{{cite news|title=The Whispers pictures|url=http://www.usnews.com/usnews/politics/whispers/paulyblog/2006/09/the_whispers_pictures.htm|first=Paul|last=Bedard|work=US News and World Report|accessdate=2006-10-16|year=2006|unused_data=September 18,}}</ref>
